      <h2>Products We've Developed</h2>
      <p>
        Our laboratory has produced two core products, both developed, tested, and refined using our purpose-built TestCell facility.
      </p>

      <h3>Hydronic Ceiling Panels</h3>
      <p>
        Suspended radiant panels capable of both heating and cooling. Modular, easy to install, and designed to fit standard Australian ceiling grids. Each panel delivers three functions in one: an insulative barrier, an embedded conditioning system, and a finished architectural surface.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/laboratory/hydronic-ceiling-panels">Learn more about hydronic ceiling panels &rarr;</a></p>

      <h3>Environmental Service Pod (ESP)</h3>
      <p>
        A consolidated, modular building services system that provides heating, cooling, hot water, and battery storage in one unit. The ESP is the first system of its kind to bring all required energy services together — designed for both new builds and retrofits.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/laboratory/environmental-service-pod">Learn more about the ESP &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
